com.pgmacdesign.pgmactips.networkclasses.retrofitutilities

Class RetrofitParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pgmacdesign.pgmactips.networkclasses.retrofitutilities.RetrofitParser

  • public class RetrofitParser
extends java.lang.Object
    Created by pmacdowell on 2017-09-11. Master Response Parser that is used for parsing calls using Call.enqueue(Callback). How to use: //Parse the response within your onTaskCompleteListener. Call call = yourServiceInterface.apiCall(params); RetrofitParser.parse(yourOnTaskCompleteListener, call, successDataModel.class, errorDataModel.class, successCallbackIntTag, failCallbackIntTag); The responses on the onTaskComplete listener will be sent back on one of the following int tags: 1) Your successCallbackIntTag 2) Your failCallbackIntTag 3) TAG_RETROFIT_PARSE_ERROR (4411) 4) TAG_RETROFIT_CALL_ERROR (4412)

    Note: If you want to send in a Type Type for these overloaded methods, use one of the examples shown in CustomConverterFactory at the top of the class

        public static final int TAG_RETROFIT_PARSE_ERROR
        This parse error tag triggers if the call could not be parsed by either the success or failure tag. If this gets sent back, the object in the OnTaskCompleteListener.onTaskComplete(Object, int) will be null.

      • TAG_RETROFIT_CALL_ERROR

        public static final int TAG_RETROFIT_CALL_ERROR
        This parse error tag triggers if the call fails or something gets caught in the Callback.onFailure(retrofit2.Call<T>, java.lang.Throwable) method. The response will always be a String of the throwable message.

    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public static void parse(@NonNull
                         OnTaskCompleteListener listener,
                         @NonNull
                         retrofit2.Call<okhttp3.ResponseBody> call,
                         java.lang.Class successClassDataModel,
                         java.lang.Class errorClassDataModel,
                         java.lang.Integer successCallbackTag,
                         java.lang.Integer failCallbackTag,
                         boolean serverCanReturn200Error)
        Parse a Call. This will run the call and attempt to parse the response NOTE! This call is Asynchronous and will run on a background thread. Data will be returned along the OnTaskCompleteListener. NOTE! Failing to add the Internet permission () in your manifest will throw the java.lang.SecurityException exception
        Parameters:
        listener - OnTaskCompleteListener To send data back on
        call - Call The call to send. Note, the type being returned must be of type ResponseBody
        successClassDataModel - Class The class data model to attempt to cast a successful response into.
        errorClassDataModel - Class The class data model to attempt to cast an unsuccessful response into.
        successCallbackTag - Integer Callback tag (enum / int) to be used if the call is Successful and parsed correctly.
        failCallbackTag - Integer Callback tag (enum / int) to be used if the call is Unsuccessful or parsed incorrectly.
        serverCanReturn200Error - This represents whether the server you are hitting can send back a 2xx response code with an error object. As most REST APIs will return a 2xx tag for a success and a 4xx for an error, this is not usually the case, but some servers will respond with a 2xx response code and have the 'error object' be considered a 'fail' response. Sending this in as true will attempt to parse the 'fail' response from both the response body as well as the response error body. If you are unsure as to wether this applies to you, start by sending false and check the responses.
